The user updates his self-description as follows: I prefer hook-driven, radio-friendly CDs—tight, glossy productions with immediate choruses, upbeat tempos, and an 80s/90s new-wave/arena-pop sheen. I especially like well-sequenced greatest-hits compilations that deliver concise, sing-along tracks and consistent sonic energy across the disc. I enjoy listening to CDs very much and collecting physical releases. Dislikes: sprawling double albums or side-long epics, long bluesy jams and meandering tracks, loose album coherence that demands extended attention, raw or muddy mixes, and records that prioritize historical heft over instant melodic payoff.

