- In short: Candidate 1 better preserves the audio characteristics I prioritize (analog warmth without loss of dynamics, tactile instrument tone, rhythm immediacy, transparent separation and natural lead vocals), while Candidate 2’s arena gloss, dense washes and tendency to overwhelm midrange vocals would materially reduce my enjoyment. For those reasons I select the Adventurous double album and reject the Studio‑polished, arena‑gloss offering.

